cat << EOF
program reads each sourcefile in sequence and parses it like a C-preprocessor,
processing all  #include, #define, #undef, #ifdef, #ifndef, #endif, #if, #elif
and  #else directives so that it can correctly tell which #include directives
would be used in a compilation.
